cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with analyzing interactions between nodes in a network over time, which is a common problem in social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes an algorithm to enumerate cliques, which involves computational complexity and optimization, making cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely categories as well. The paper also discusses the practical relevance of the proposed algorithm, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
